y Life&quot;</font></b></h1>\r</center><center><h3><font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><b>Instructor: \rAlfred Kobsa</b></font></h3></center>\r<center>\r  <p><font face=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"><b>kobsa @ uci.edu , Rm. CS 430C, \r    Bldg. 302</b></font><br>\r    <br>\r  </p>\r  <p align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\r  <p align=\"left\"><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> These are guidelines intended\r    to help students plan their work in this course. However, the instructor\r    does reserve the right to make changes if needed.\r  </p>\r</center>\r<p><b>General \rEducational Aims: </b>This course gives a gentle introduction to the &quot;people's\rside of computers&quot;, and to the potential future role of computers in our everyday\rlives.\r<p><b>Requirements</b>: None. Enrollment will be restricted to freshmen\r  until Thursday, noon, March 24, 2005. After this date, enrollment in Uni Stu\r  3 will be open to ALL undergraduates.\r<p><b>Character of course</b>: We will read the textbook and discuss about it.\r  Students will give presentations on chapters of the textbook.\r<p><b>Time and Location</b>: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Fridays&nbsp;2pm-2:50pm&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Room\r  432 in the CS building (bldg 302).<br>\r  <br>\r<b>Required readings</b>: \r<ul>\r  <li>Ben Shneiderman: <em>Leonardo's Laptop: Human Needs and the New Computing\r      Technologies</em>.\r    MIT Press, 2003; ISBN: 0262692996<I> <br>\r    </I>(See UCI\r                        bookstore or reserve in\r                        the  Science Library; <a href=\"http://www.addall.com/New/Partner.cgi?type=ISBN&query=0262692996\">compare\r                        mail-order\r                        prices</a>)<br>\r                        <em>\r                        </em> </li>\r</ul>\r<TABLE WIDTH=\"1130\" BORDER=\"0\"><TR><TD WIDTH=\"78\"><B>Grading:</B></TD>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"306\">50% for presentation</TD>\r    <TD ROWSPAN=\"3\" WIDTH=\"732\">&nbsp;</TD>\r  </TR><TR><TD WIDTH=\"78\">&nbsp;</TD>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"306\">50% \rfor participation in discussions</TD>\r    </TR>\r  <TR><TD WIDTH=\"78\">&nbsp;</TD>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"306\">&nbsp;</TD>\r  </TR>\r  </TABLE>\r<p><b>Efficient reading</b>: see <a href=\"../../efficientReading.pdf\">here<br>\r  <br>\r</a><b>Cheating</b>: see <a href=\"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~ucounsel/continuing_students/cheat.html\">here<b><br>\r  </b></a><strong><br>\r  Students with Disabilities:</strong> see <a href=\"../../ICS104/general/disabilities.htm\">here</a> \r<p><b>Add/drop Deadlines</b>:&nbsp;&nbsp; 5:00pm the second week of classes (April\r15, 2005). I'll be happy to sign drop cards thereafter though.\r<p><b>Office hours: </b>by arrangement<B> </B>(contact me in class or send\remail beforehand). \r<p><br> \r  <b>Syllabus</b>: \r  <FONT COLOR=\"#ED181E\"> <FONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif\"> </FONT></FONT><table BORDER=3 WIDTH=\"81%\" BORDERCOLOR=\"#330000\" >\r  <tr> \r    <td width=\"4%\"><DIV ALIGN=\"CENTER\"><b>Unit </b></DIV></td>\r    <td width=\"20%\"><b>Date</b></td>\r    <td width=\"39%\"><b>Topic</b></td>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"37%\"><B>Reading chapter</B></TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr> \r    <td width=\"4%\">&nbsp;1</td>\r    <td width=\"20%\"><div align=\"left\">&nbsp;4/8</div></td>\r    <td width=\"39%\">Introduction</td>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"37%\">Chapter 1</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr> \r    <td width=\"4%\">&nbsp;2</td>\r    <td width=\"20%\"><div align=\"left\"> 4/15</div></td>\r    <td width=\"39%\">Unusable at any bandwidth</td>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"37%\">Chapter 2</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr> \r    <td width=\"4%\">&nbsp;3</td>\r    <td width=\"20%\"><div align=\"left\">4/22</div></td>\r    <td width=\"39%\">The quest for universal usability</td>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"37%\">Chapter 3</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr> \r    <td width=\"4%\">&nbsp;4</td>\r    <td width=\"20%\"><div align=\"left\">4/29</div></td>\r    <td width=\"39%\">New methods, new goals</td>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"37%\">Chapter 4</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td>&nbsp;</td>\r    <td>5/6</td>\r    <td>Understanding human activities and relationships</td>\r    <TD>Chapter 5</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr> \r    <td width=\"4%\">&nbsp;5</td>\r    <td width=\"20%\"><div align=\"left\">5/13</div></td>\r    <td width=\"39%\">e-Learning</td>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"37%\">Chapter 6</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr> \r    <td width=\"4%\">&nbsp;6</td>\r    <td width=\"20%\"><div align=\"left\">10/19</div></td>\r    <td width=\"39%\">e-Business</td>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"37%\">Chapter 7</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr> \r    <td width=\"4%\"> &nbsp;7</td>\r    <td width=\"20%\"><div align=\"left\">10/21</div></td>\r    <td width=\"39%\"> e-Healthcare</td>\r    <TD WIDTH=\"37%\">Chapter 8</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td>&nbsp;8</td>\r    <td><div align=\"left\">10/26</div>\r    </td>\r    <td>e-Government</td>\r    <TD>Chapter 9</TD>\r  </tr>\r  <tr>\r    <td>9</td>\r    <td><div align=\"left\">10/28</div>\r    </td>\r    <td>Creativity</td>\r    <TD>Chapter 10</TD>\r  </tr>\r</table>\r<p>&nbsp;\r</body>\r</html>\r", "encoding": "ascii"}